		<title>
		By: Brent Fleming		</title>
		<link>https://jamesclear.com/workout-journal#comment-12366</link>

		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Brent Fleming]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 29 Oct 2014 19:56:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://jamesclear-com.uar9g7bv-liquidwebsites.com/?p=6247#comment-12366</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[I use the app &quot;Bodyspace&quot;.  It gives you different programs to choose from so there is no wasting time when you go to the gym. Just hit the day you want to track and you are good to go. It&#039;s so simple to record weight and reps. Just enter in right after you complete the set. This keeps track of of which set you are on. Can&#039;t remember what you did for weight on this exercise last time, just click on history of exercise and instantly gives you what weight you did last time. Want to know your one rep maximum. click on one rep max in that exercise. If you want to substitute another shoulder exercise than the one in the program click on shoulder exercises. It will give you up to 50 different exercises to choose from. Don&#039;t know how to do that exercise? Click on the video and it shows you how to do it. At the end of the workout it adds up sets, reps and the amount of weight you just pushed. Go to your history and find out how much weight you&#039;ve pushed overall throughout the entire program. I never worked out consistently for my 40 years. I found this app and now I workout five times a week. I am now going into my 16th week of working out consistently and I am on my second program. This app keeps track of everything. Best thing about it is I waste no time at the gym thinking about what I&#039;m going to do or writing stuff down. My workouts are done in about an hour. This is an awesome workout app, I would highly recommend checking it out.

Cheers,

Brent]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I use the app &#8220;Bodyspace&#8221;.  It gives you different programs to choose from so there is no wasting time when you go to the gym. Just hit the day you want to track and you are good to go. It&#8217;s so simple to record weight and reps. Just enter in right after you complete the set. This keeps track of of which set you are on. Can&#8217;t remember what you did for weight on this exercise last time, just click on history of exercise and instantly gives you what weight you did last time. Want to know your one rep maximum. click on one rep max in that exercise. If you want to substitute another shoulder exercise than the one in the program click on shoulder exercises. It will give you up to 50 different exercises to choose from. Don&#8217;t know how to do that exercise? Click on the video and it shows you how to do it. At the end of the workout it adds up sets, reps and the amount of weight you just pushed. Go to your history and find out how much weight you&#8217;ve pushed overall throughout the entire program. I never worked out consistently for my 40 years. I found this app and now I workout five times a week. I am now going into my 16th week of working out consistently and I am on my second program. This app keeps track of everything. Best thing about it is I waste no time at the gym thinking about what I&#8217;m going to do or writing stuff down. My workouts are done in about an hour. This is an awesome workout app, I would highly recommend checking it out.</p>
<p>Cheers,</p>
<p>Brent</p>
