					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jamesclear.com/workout-journal#comment-12332&quot;&gt;Ryan Fuse&lt;/a&gt;.

Each vertical line signals the completion of one set. Say you&#039;re doing 5 sets of 3 reps. I pick up the weight, do 3 reps, put the weight back, and make a tally mark. It&#039;s just a quick way of marking, &quot;1 set down, 4 to go.&quot;]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://jamesclear.com/workout-journal#comment-12332">Ryan Fuse</a>.</p>
<p>Each vertical line signals the completion of one set. Say you&#8217;re doing 5 sets of 3 reps. I pick up the weight, do 3 reps, put the weight back, and make a tally mark. It&#8217;s just a quick way of marking, &#8220;1 set down, 4 to go.&#8221;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
